                    h1 Events aggregator
                    h5.light.
                        Events aggregator used to calculate the aggregated percentage for events that have occurred.
        main
            div.row
                div.col.s12.m10.offset-m1
                    h3 Events aggregator description
                    p.
                        Events aggregator used to calculate the percentage of objects from a group of objects for which 
                        an event occurred. For example, you can send emergency notifications to administrators when a certain 
                        percentage of servers in a cluster providing a service are no longer available.
                    h3 Parameters
                    ul.browser-default
                        li.
                            Object group name or objectID of group - the name of the object group or the group objectID for 
                            which the aggregated check will be performed
                        li.
                            Event counter name or counterID - the name of the event counter or counterID for which the 
                            aggregated check will be performed. Event generator must be installed as a collector for this counter.
                    h3 Returned value
                    p.
                        The percentage of objects from the total number of objects in the group for which the event occurred.
